1️⃣ LOGICAL REASONING – BLOOD RELATIONS

This is a very common placement topic.
Questions test your ability to understand family relationships logically.

🔹 A. BASIC RELATIONS (MUST KNOW)
Father / Mother
Brother / Sister
Son / Daughter
Uncle / Aunt
Grandfather / Grandmother
🔹 B. KEY APPROACH (VERY IMPORTANT)

👉 Always:

Draw a family tree (diagram)
Solve step-by-step
Don’t guess
🔹 Example 1

A is the father of B.
B is the sister of C.

👉 What is A to C?

Solution:
A → father of B
B → sister of C

So A is father of C ✅

🔹 Example 2

P is the brother of Q.
Q is the mother of R.

👉 What is P to R?

P → brother of Q
Q → mother of R

So P = uncle of R ✅

🔹 Example 3 (Tricky)

A is the son of B.
B is the daughter of C.

👉 What is A to C?

A → son of B
B → daughter of C

So A = grandson of C ✅

🔹 C. SYMBOL TYPE QUESTIONS

Sometimes symbols are used:

A + B → A is father of B
A − B → A is mother of B
A × B → A is brother of B
🔹 Example 4

A + B × C

B × C → B is brother of C
A + B → A is father of B

So A is also father of C ✅

📝 PRACTICE QUESTIONS
A is mother of B, B is brother of C. What is A to C?
P is father of Q, Q is sister of R. What is P to R?
A is brother of B, B is mother of C. What is A to C?
X + Y, Y × Z. What is X to Z?
A is daughter of B, B is son of C. What is A to C?
